         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... In (all bi)rth circles may the pure spirit never disappear for me! 36. (Through the) wri(ting of the Sukhavarga) ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Möge mir in allen Geburtenreihen das reine Denken niemals vergehen!</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">May clear thinking never leave me in all sequences of births!</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>114</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May I vanquish the untamed [and] shameless spirit, may I subjugate all the passions! ... the hurting ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">through (body, spe)ech [and] spirit may I always evolve according to the Law that has been taught by the good ones! (37.) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... May all the beings of the five births be able to tame [their] spirit (in) all (the births)! ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... May I myself recognize the five elements [= the five skandhas] that ought to be known! And may I not cling [to them]! (38.) ... (For sure my wish may be fulfilled!)</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Die fünf zu wissenden Skandhas möchte ich [als] höchstes Ziel erkennen [und] nicht [daran] haften!</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The five skandhas to know I want to recognize [as] the highest aim [and] not cling [to them]!</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>108</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May I have a pure way of living [lit. living of life] consisting of wisdom by this three-fold deed! (Avoiding) su(ffering and happiness in the sharing ... (May I avoid the danger of the) </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(pass)ions, [and] may I always become without anger through this deed! 39. (Which [= the Brāhmaṇavarga] makes rain jewels of meanings like) the cintāmaṇi (gem), </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1 #b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Den wie das Cintāmaṇi-Juwel Besitzesperlen regnen lassenden vorzüglichen [und] (aller)ausgezeichnetsten Brāhmaṇavarga habe ich mit [diesem] guten Wunsch geschrieben: Den achtgliedrigen edlen Pfad, der zur Nirvāṇa-Stadt führt, möchte ich offenbar machen! Das Glück des Erlöschens aller Leiden möchten die Fünfgeburtenwesen erlangen durch meinen eigenen Wunsch.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">The excellent [and] (most) splendid Brāhmaṇavarga, which, like the Cintāmaṇi jewel lets rain possession-pearls, I have written with [this] good wish: may I make evident the eight-part noble path that leads to the city of nirvāṇa! May the beings of the five incarnations attain the bliss of extinction of all suffering through my own wish.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>349-50, 451-2</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">I have written the (excellent) Brāhmaṇavarga, (super)ior (to everything, may I make manifest) the noble eightfold path (that goes to the city of Nirvāṇa!) </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">May [the beings] (of the five births) reach the happiness (consisting in the extinction of all sufferings) through the wish coming from me! 40. (Some) say also that: ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">through love [and] belief in the omniscient. How many ak(ṣaras there are) in the book ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... through the Law [and] faithfullness. 41. In the regnal year of the growing k(ing) of the kings ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... by a great wish, through the fruit of this deed (may) the be(ings) of the five births ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
